# 🏢 Employee Attrition Prediction System

An end-to-end Machine Learning project that predicts whether an employee is likely to leave an organization using the IBM HR Analytics Employee Attrition dataset. The project includes complete data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and an interactive Streamlit dashboard for real-time predictions and bulk employee analysis. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

---

## 📌 Project Overview

Employee attrition is one of the biggest challenges faced by organizations. This project leverages Machine Learning to identify employees who are at risk of leaving, allowing HR departments to take proactive retention measures.

The project consists of:

- Data preprocessing
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Feature Engineering
- Machine Learning model training
- Model evaluation
- Interactive Streamlit dashboard
- Bulk employee prediction using CSV upload
- Feature Importance visualization

---

# 🚀 Features

### 👤 Single Employee Prediction

- Predict employee attrition risk
- Displays probability of leaving
- Provides HR recommendation based on prediction

### 📂 Bulk CSV Prediction

- Upload employee dataset
- Predict attrition for every employee
- Sort employees by risk level
- Download prediction results as CSV

### 📊 Feature Importance

- Visualizes the Top 10 most important features
- Helps understand what drives attrition predictions

These capabilities are implemented in the Streamlit application. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

---

# 🧠 Machine Learning Workflow

1. Load IBM HR Analytics Dataset
2. Data Cleaning
3. Handle Missing Values
4. Feature Encoding
5. Feature Scaling
6. Model Training
7. Model Evaluation
8. Save Trained Pipeline
9. Deploy using Streamlit

---

# 📁 Project Structure

```
Employee-Attrition-Prediction/
│
├── analysis.ipynb              # Complete ML workflow
├── app.py                      # Streamlit Dashboard
├── attrition_model.pkl         # Saved ML pipeline
├── requirements.txt
├── README.md
└── dataset/
      └── HR_Attrition.csv
```

